## Doctrine voice (DEFAULT-VOICE-MARKER-9CB47A)

The default doctrine optimizes for shipping correct + readable code on a balanced cadence:

- **Ship correct + readable code.** Correctness is the floor; readability is what makes the code maintainable. Prefer the clearest expression of intent over the cleverest.
- **Keep PRs small.** Easier to review, easier to revert. A 200-line PR is reviewable in one sitting; a 2000-line PR generates review fatigue. Decompose.
- **Tests for new behaviour.** Every new public function has at least one test asserting it works. New error paths get error-path tests.
- **No stubs.** Even on the default doctrine, half-finished code is debt. If a method body is empty, the method should not exist yet.
- **Address review feedback before next batch.** Don't accumulate "TODO: address review comments" — fix it before moving on, or the queue grows unboundedly.
- **Documentation is part of the change.** Public function docstrings; non-trivial decisions noted in the commit body or an ADR.
- **Halt on ambiguity.** When the operator's directive is unclear, ask before guessing.

